  "text": "Now, symmetry requires all descendants to be present in the OPE and this implies that the order of the pole in z orz cannot be bounded from above because a, b can be arbitrarily large positive integers. But, this is practically impossible because in the present situation the leading pole can be obtained by Mellin transforming the splitting function in the collinear limit [1] [2] [CITATION_1] . So it seems reasonable to assume that the order of the pole in z orz will be bounded from above and therefore, we should impose the condition (8.3) on the primary φ h,h .",
